  "body": "# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, we can provide multiple endpoints for the `--beacon-rpc` validator client parameter, but the implementation assumes they share identical connection requirements (specifically `--tls-cert` and `--grpc-headers` options).\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nIt would be helpful to be able to specify per-endpoint options for `--tls-cert` and `--grpc-headers`, including the ability to have a local insecure (no TLS and no GRPC Headers required) and a remote (using TLS and GRPC Headers) beacon mix. The solution should be generic enough to allow specifying NONE or distinct values for these params per-endpoint for maximum flexibility.\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\nNothing practical.",
